commit.message: switch to using a src dir, and updates for pytest4
not needed since restricted to python 3.5+
add pypy3 to travis ci conf
update travis to run tox tests using tox-travis
updates to support Tornado 5 (older versions no longer supported), and test improvements
use 127.0.0.1 for test client connections, like tornado itself does now too

fix for coroutine tests, and no Internet access

 - coroutine tests that didn't use the io_loop fixture work now
 - http tests use local server only to avoid slowness due to
   clogged tubes
syntax-highlighting in readme, and tweaks to examples
require python 3.5+, and switch to alpha status before putting on pypi
don't import plugin explicitly, but rely on it being installed
